The easiest way to get started with your own Chef server is to launch a fully-functional Amazon Machine Images (AMI) for the Chef server from the AWS Marketplace or get Chef server from the Microsoft Azure Marketplace.

Both the AMI and Azure Marketplace image are preconfigured with Chef server, the [Chef management console](https://docs.chef.io/manage.html), [Chef reporting](https://docs.chef.io/install_reporting.html), and [Chef Analytics](https://docs.chef.io/analytics.html).

You can also install Chef server manually on your own hardware or on another cloud provider.

[COMMENT] If you choose the AMI or the Azure Marketplace image, the documentation you'll follow recommends extracting the Starter Kit to a directory named <% fp 'chef-repo/.chef' %>. If you followed other Learn Chef tutorials, you can extract the Starter Kit to the <% fp '~/learn-chef' %> directory, which will create a full path named <% fp '~/learn-chef/chef-repo/.chef' %>.

